  "text": "To determine whether changes in photoperiod also regulate dmpi8 splicing, wild-type CS flies were kept at 18°C and exposed for several days at two different photoperiods (6:18LD and 12:12LD) (Fig. 1) . First, we assayed the effects of variations in photoperiod on total per mRNA levels. RNA levels were mainly determined by semiquantitative RT-PCR ( (36), total per mRNA levels accumulated earlier during the day and reached higher peak values as a function of shortening the duration of the photoperiod ( Fig. 1B and E ). An earlier accumulation phase for per mRNA levels under shorter photoperiods was also previously observed at the standard temperature of 25°C [CITATION_1] .",
